🌍 IoT Based Environmental Monitoring System






📌 About

This project is a simple IoT system that monitors environmental conditions like air quality, gas leakage, temperature, and humidity in real time.

It shows data:

📟 On an LCD (device itself)
📱 On a dashboard (phone/laptop)

We also added small readable messages so users don’t have to understand raw values.

⚙️ What it does

✨ Real-time monitoring
🌫️ Air quality tracking
🔥 Gas leakage detection
🌡️ Temperature & humidity sensing
📊 Live dashboard updates
🚨 Alerts using buzzer

🧰 Components
🔹 Hardware
ESP8266 / ESP32
MQ135 (Air Quality)
MQ2 / MQ6 (Gas Sensor)
DHT11 / DHT22
16x2 LCD
Buzzer
Breadboard & wires
🔹 Software
Arduino IDE
ThingSpeak / Blynk
🔄 Working
Sensors → ESP → LCD
             ↓
          WiFi → Cloud → Dashboard
Sensors collect data
ESP processes it
LCD shows local values
Cloud shows remote values
Alerts trigger when needed
📊 Parameters
Parameter	Sensor	Unit
🌡️ Temperature	DHT11/22	°C
💧 Humidity	DHT11/22	%
🌫️ Air Quality	MQ135	AQI
🔥 Gas	MQ2/MQ6	PPM
💡 Smart Messages

Instead of just numbers, system shows:

✅ Air quality is good
⚠️ Air quality is moderate
🔴 Air quality is poor
🚨 Gas leakage detected!
🚀 Setup
1. Install Arduino IDE
2. Connect ESP + sensors
3. Add WiFi credentials in code
4. Upload code
5. Open dashboard
⚠️ Issues faced
Sensor calibration took time
MQ sensors unstable initially
WiFi disconnections sometimes
🔮 Future scope
Mobile app 📱
ML-based prediction 🤖
More sensors (PM2.5)
Better accuracy
