IoT Based Environmental Monitoring System
About

This project monitors basic environmental conditions using IoT.
We used sensors to measure air quality, gas leakage, temperature, and humidity, and send the data online.

The system shows readings on an LCD and also on a dashboard so it can be checked remotely.

Features
Real-time monitoring
Air quality and gas detection
Temperature and humidity tracking
LCD display + online dashboard
Basic alert system using buzzer
Components

Hardware

ESP8266 / ESP32
MQ135 (air quality)
MQ2 / MQ6 (gas sensor)
DHT11 / DHT22
16x2 LCD
Buzzer

Software

Arduino IDE
ThingSpeak / Blynk
Working

Sensors collect data → ESP processes it →

shows on LCD
sends to cloud via WiFi

If values cross limits, buzzer turns ON.

Parameters
Temperature (°C)
Humidity (%)
Air Quality (AQI / PPM)
Gas Level (PPM)
Setup
Connect sensors to ESP
Open code in Arduino IDE
Add WiFi credentials
Upload code
Open dashboard
Issues faced
Sensor calibration
Fluctuating readings
Network issues sometimes
Future scope
Add mobile app
Improve accuracy
Add more sensors
